Charting/Modding Info
Note: I'm a o!m Mapper

I make levels... Scroll down to the Beatmaps thing at the bottom of this webpage... you'll see it. I know you will.

Favorite the charts you like most of mine. I will chart similar things depending on the most demanded types of songs/charting

Poke me in-game for a M4M GD or NM mod.

<3 Kobaryo & Camellia
The PP System
It is impossible to loose overall PP. If you've done a bad accuracy on a chart but did a better score the PP of that chart will go down, BUT the PP of all your other charts will go up thus NOT lowering your PP. NOTE: RANK IS NOT PP!!! The leaderboard has a large delay & should not be used as a exact measurement of skill. The End!
How to get good within 6 months


1. play at least up to 3* [4k] so you are able to at least read notes properly.
2. Make sure you have your BPM scroll to something 22 or higher (Depending on the skin)
3. Turn on nofail & play 6* levels. Stay on this step until you can keep up with the notes with at least 78% accuracy
4. Turn off nofail & turn on the easy mod. The hit window will be larger thus building up your confidence. Play with this until you can get 85% accuracy
5. Turn off all mods. At this point 6* levels should be almost passable or barely passable. Stay at this step until you can 90% some (Not most) 6* charts
6. Go play 4* charts to improve your accuracy. Play at least two 6* levels per session.
7. Progress to higher star levels with the S rank. After practicing accuracy on 4* levels & speed on 6* levels you should be able to S most 5* levels.
8. Try to improve your skill using the Dan scale. If you can't beat a dan then practice harder charts until you can
9. Make friends if you haven't yet. The hell hole that you put yourself into will become boring after a year. A person to talk to would help you improve. (Don't ask me about this step lol)
10. By now you should already be good at the game. The rest is up to you.

Things that don't require gameplay that still improves your overall performance.
1. Do reverse wrist curls [How to do them-> She has bigger muscles than you. wtf is wrong with you weakling?

2. Stretch. This warms up your muscles & loosens them. It also allows you to get more improvement from all above steps
3. Be confident in your skills & improvement. Be positive & never negative.
4. Always enjoy osu,!mania or other vsrg games. The instant you start to blame the game is also the instant you start to do worse at it.

I've done all the steps above & got whats considered good in 6 months. Just because you achieved everything on this list doesnt mean there is no room for improvement. There are still 12* levels you can't beat. Keep getting better xD

[box=The PP System][b]It is impossible to loose overall PP. If you've done a bad accuracy on a chart but did a better score the PP of that chart will go down, BUT the PP of all your other charts will go up thus NOT lowering your PP. NOTE: RANK IS NOT PP!!! The leaderboard has a large delay & should not be used as a exact measurement of skill. The End![/b][/box]

[box=How to get good within 6 months][img]http://puu.sh/s7QS8.JPG[/img]

1. play at least up to 3* [4k] so you are able to at least read notes properly. 
2. Make sure you have your BPM scroll to something 22 or higher (Depending on the skin)
3. Turn on nofail & play 6* levels. Stay on this step until you can keep up with the notes with at least 78% accuracy
4. Turn off nofail & turn on the easy mod. The hit window will be larger thus building up your confidence. Play with this until you can get 85% accuracy
5. Turn off all mods. At this point 6* levels should be almost passable or barely passable. Stay at this step until you can 90% some (Not most) 6* charts
6. Go play 4* charts to improve your accuracy. Play at least two 6* levels per session.
7. Progress to higher star levels with the S rank. After practicing accuracy on 4* levels & speed on 6* levels you should be able to S most 5* levels. 
8. Try to improve your skill using the Dan scale. If you can't beat a dan then practice harder charts until you can
9. Make friends if you haven't yet. The hell hole that you put yourself into will become boring after a year. A person to talk to would help you improve. (Don't ask me about this step lol)
10. By now you should already be good at the game. The rest is up to you.

[u]Things that don't require gameplay that still improves your overall performance.[/u]
1. Do reverse wrist curls [How to do them-> She has bigger muscles than you. wtf is wrong with you weakling? [youtube]krZ6pWGZ8xo[/youtube]
2. Stretch. This warms up your muscles & loosens them. It also allows you to get more improvement from all above steps
3. Be confident in your skills & improvement. Be positive & never negative.
4. Always enjoy osu,!mania or other vsrg games. The instant you start to blame the game is also the instant you start to do worse at it.

I've done all the steps above & got whats considered good in 6 months. Just because you achieved everything on this list doesnt mean there is no room for improvement. There are still 12* levels you can't beat. Keep getting better xD[/box][/notice]
